    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/bitcoin-dev/2023-October/004174.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The email discusses the use of the OP_Expire opcode in Bitcoin programming and its application in HTLC protocols. It suggests that OP_Expire can be added to the pre-image branch of the script in HTLC protocols to set a deadline for transactions requiring the preimage to be revealed on-chain. The email also mentions the option of encoding expiration heights as a delta against a block-height nLockTime, instead of using a specific Coinbase Bit. This alternative approach would involve checking the absolute expiration height with OP_Expire. Overall, the email emphasizes the flexibility and security provided by OP_Expire in enforcing time constraints for certain transactions in HTLC protocols.</summary>
